functools32.description: functools32 includes new features lru_cache (Least-recently-used cache decorator).
functools32.summary: Backport of the functools module from Python 3.2.3 for use on 2.7 and PyPy.

functools_lru_cache.summary: Backport of functools.lru_cache from Python 3.3 as published at ActiveState.

jupyter.description: Jupyter Notebook is a web application, a browser-based tool for interactive authoring of documents which combine explanatory text, mathematics, computations and their rich media output.
jupyter.summary: Jupyter metapackage. Install all the Jupyter components in one go.

jupyter_client.description: jupyter client contains the reference implementation of the Jupyter protocol.It also provides Python API for starting, managing and communicating with Jupyter kernels.
jupyter_client.summary: Jupyter protocol implementation and client libraries

jupyter_console.description: Jupyter console is a terminal frontend for kernels using the Jupyter protocol.

jupyter_core.description: This package defines the core common functionality of Jupyter projects.
jupyter_core.summary: Core common functionality of Jupyter projects.

jupyter_dashboards_bundlers.description: The dashbaords bundler extension takes a notebook with layout information from the dashboard layout extention and lets you download it or directly publish it to the experimental dashboard server.

openresty.summary: Turning Nginx into a Full-Fledged Scriptable Web Platform

openssl.summary: OpenSSL is an open-source implementation of the SSL and TLS protocols

opentracing.description: opentracing-python provides only the API and a basic no-op implementation that can be used by instrumentation libraries to collect and propagate distributed tracing context

protobuf.description: Protocol buffers are Google's language-neutral, platform-neutral, extensible mechanism for serializing structured data,think XML, but smaller, faster, and simpler.
protobuf.summary: Protocol Buffers - Google's data interchange format.

pscript.summary: library for transpiling Python code to JavaScript.

psutil.description: psutil (process and system utilities) is a cross-platform library for retrieving information on running processes and system utilization (CPU, memory, disks, network) in Python. It is useful mainly for system monitoring, profiling and limiting process resources and management of running processes.
psutil.summary: A cross-platform process and system utilities module for Python

psycopg2.description: Psycopg is the most popular PostgreSQL adapter for the Python programming language. Its main features are the complete implementation of the Python DB API 2.0 specification and the thread safety.

py-opencv.description: OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision Library) includes several hundreds of computer vision algorithms. It has a modular structure,which means that the package includes several shared or static libraries.
py-opencv.summary: Computer vision and machine learning software library.

pytest.description: The pytest framework makes it easy to write small tests, yet scales to support complex functional testing for applications and libraries.
pytest.summary: Simple and powerful testing with Python.

pytest-arraydiff.description: This is a py.test plugin to facilitate the generation and comparison of data arrays produced during tests.
pytest-arraydiff.summary: pytest plugin to help with comparing array output from tests

pytest-astropy.description: This is a meta-package that pulls in the dependencies that are used by astropy and some affiliated packages for testing. It can also be used for testing packages that are not affiliated with the Astropy project.
pytest-astropy.summary: Meta-package containing dependencies for testing Astropy

pytest-base-url.summary: pytest plugin for URL based testing

pytest-benchmark.summary: A py.test fixture for benchmarking code

pytest-cache.description: NOTE: pytest-cache is no longer maintained since its functionality was integrated into pytest core starting with pytest-2.8.0.
pytest-cache.summary: pytest plugin with mechanisms for caching across test runs

pytest-cov.description: pytest-cov produces coverage reports.It supports centralised testing and distributed testing in both load and each modes.It also supports coverage of subprocesses.

pytest-doctestplus.description: This package contains a plugin for the pytest framework that provides advanced doctest support and enables the testing of reStructuredText files.
pytest-doctestplus.summary: Pytest plugin with advanced doctest features

pytest-forked.summary: run tests in isolated forked subprocesses

pytest-html.summary: pytest plugin for generating HTML reports

pytest-json.description: pytest-json is a plugin for py.test that generates JSON reports for test results.

pytest-localserver.summary: pytest-localserver is a plugin for the pytest testing framework which enables you to test server connections locally.

pytest-metadata.summary: pytest plugin for test session metadata

pytest-mock.summary: Thin-wrapper around the mock package for easier use with py.test

pytest-openfiles.description: This package provides a plugin for the pytest framework that allows developers to detect whether any file handles or other file-like objects were inadvertently left open at the end of a unit test.
pytest-openfiles.summary: Pytest plugin for detecting inadvertent open file handles

pytest-pep8.description: py.test plugin for efficiently checking PEP8 compliance.
pytest-pep8.summary: py.test plugin for efficiently checking PEP8 compliance

pytest-remotedata.description: This package provides a plugin for the pytest framework that allows developers to control unit tests that require access to data from the internet.
pytest-remotedata.summary: Pytest plugin for controlling remote data access

pytest-runner.summary: Invoke py.test as distutils command with dependency resolution.

pytest-selenium.summary: pytest-selenium is a plugin for py.test that provides support for running Selenium based tests.

pytest-timeout.description: pytest-timeout is a plugin which will terminate tests after a certain timeout. When doing so it will show a stack dump of all threads running at the time.
pytest-timeout.summary: This is a plugin which will terminate tests after a certain timeout.

pytest-tornado.summary: A py.test plugin providing fixtures and markers to simplify testing of asynchronous tornado applications.

pytest-variables.summary: pytest plugin for providing variables to tests/fixtures

pytest-xdist.summary: py.test xdist plugin for distributed testing and loop-on-failing modes

python.description: Python is a widely used high-level, general-purpose, interpreted, dynamic programming language. Its design philosophy emphasizes code readability, and its syntax allows programmers to express concepts in fewer lines of code than would be possible in languages such as C++ or Java. The language provides constructs intended to enable clear programs on both a small and large scale.

python-blosc.summary: A Python wrapper for the extremely fast Blosc compression library

python-chromedriver-binary.description: WebDriver is an open source tool for automated testing of webapps across many browsers. It provides capabilities for navigating to web pages, user input, JavaScript execution, and more.  ChromeDriver is a standalone server which implements WebDriver's wire protocol for Chromium.

setuptools.description: Setuptools is a fully-featured, actively-maintained, and stable library designed to facilitate packaging Python projects.
setuptools.summary: Download, build, install, upgrade, and uninstall Python packages

setuptools-git.summary: Setuptools revision control system plugin for Git

setuptools_scm.summary: The blessed package to manage your versions by scm tags.

sh.description: sh is a full-fledged subprocess interface for Python that allows you to call any program as if it were a function.

shapely.summary: Python package for manipulation and analysis of geometric objects in the Cartesian plane.

simplegeneric.description: The simplegeneric module lets you define simple single-dispatch generic functions, akin to Python's built-in generic functions like len(), iter() and so on. However, instead of using specially-named methods, these generic functions use simple lookup tables, akin to those used by e.g. pickle.dump() and other generic functions found in the Python standard library.
simplegeneric.summary: Simple generic functions (similar to Python's own len(), pickle.dump(), etc.)

simplejson.description: simplejson is a simple, fast, complete, correct and extensible JSON <http://json.org> encoder and decoder for Python 2.5+ and Python 3.3+. It is pure Python code with no dependencies, but includes an optional C extension for a serious speed boost.
simplejson.summary: Simple, fast, extensible JSON encoder/decoder for Python

singledispatch.description: This library brings functools.singledispatch from Python 3.4 to Python 2.6-3.3.
singledispatch.summary: Transforms a function into a single-dispatch generic function

sip.description: SIP is a tool that makes it very easy to create Python bindings for C and C++ libraries. SIP comprises a code generator and a Python module. The code generator processes a set of specification files and generates C or C++ code which is then compiled to create the bindings extension module. The SIP Python module provides support functions to the automatically generated code.
sip.summary: Create Python bindings for C and C++ libraries

six.description: Six provides simple utilities for wrapping over differences between Python 2 and Python 3. It is intended to support codebases that work on both Python 2 and 3 without modification. six consists of only one Python file, so it is painless to copy into a project.

smart_open.description: smart_open is a Python 2 & Python 3 library for efficient streaming of very large files from/to S3, HDFS, WebHDFS or local (compressed) files.
smart_open.summary: Python library for efficient streaming of large files

urllib3.description: urllib3 is a powerful, sanity-friendly HTTP client for Python. Much of the Python ecosystem already uses urllib3. urllib3 brings many critical features that are missing from the Python standard libraries, such as thread safety, connection pooling, client side ssl/tls verification, support for gzip and deflate encodings, HTTP and SOCKS proxy support, helpers for retrying requests and dealing with HTTP redirects.
urllib3.summary: HTTP library with thread-safe connection pooling, file post, and more.
